Package system

Class RegistrationSystem

java.lang.Object
system.RegistrationSystem
public class RegistrationSystem extends Object
The RegistrationSystem class stores information about the school, including the ability to add students, add faculty, add courses, and add prerequisite(s).

    • addSection

      public void addSection(SubjectCode code, int courseNum, int sectionNum, String firstName, String lastName, Quarter quarter, int year, int cap, Building bldg, String room) throws CourseNotFoundException, PersonNotFoundException, DuplicateSectionException
      Adds a section to the section list collection.
      Parameters:
      code - The subject code of the course
      courseNum - The course number of the course
      sectionNum - The section number for the course
      firstName - The first name for the faculty teaching the course
      lastName - The last name for the faculty teaching the course
      quarter - The quarter that the course section is held
      year - The year that the course section is held
      cap - The capacity of the course section
      bldg - The building that the course section is held
      room - The room that the course section is held
      Throws:
      CourseNotFoundException - The course was not found in the system
      PersonNotFoundException - The person was not found in the system
      DuplicateSectionException - The section is already in the system
